{
  "texts": [
    "After two rounds of annotation, we reached substantial inter-rater agreement (Cohen's κ = 0.87).",
    "A chi-square test was performed to examine the relation between human perception of anthropomorphism and inferred anthropomorphism measured via high A scores (thresholding at the average A score in the respective set; randomly-sampled set: avg(A) = -3.28, stratified set: avg(A) = 1.32).",
    "Within both sets, higher than average A is significantly more likely among sentences humans judged to contain anthropomorphism (randomlysampled set: χ 2 = 17.98, p < 0.00001; stratified set: χ 2 = 11.26, p < 0.001).",
    "Complete details and full distributions of scores are in Appendix C.1.",
    "Correlation with LIWC As another measure of validity, we examine correlations between A and dimensions of LIWC-22."
  ]
}